videoSnippet.title: U.S. Girl's Champion Becomes U.S. Women's Champion!
videoSnippet.description:
Photos by Lennart Ootes https://www.chessphotoshop.com/
Have a great day :)

Krush, Irina (2432) - Yu, Jennifer (2297) 
U.S. Women's Championship (chess24.com) [16] 2022.10.20
A07 Reti, King's Indian attack, Pachman system

1.Nf3 d5 2.g3 g6 3.Bg2 Bg7 4.O-O e5 5.d3 Ne7 6.Nbd2 O-O 7.e4 d4 8.Ne1 Nbc6 9.f4 Bg4 10.Qxg4 f5 11.Qe2 Qd7 12.Nef3 Rae8 13.fxe5 Nxe5 14.Nxe5 Bxe5 15.exf5 Nxf5 16.Ne4 b6 17.Bd2 c5 18.Rf2 Re7 19.Raf1 Rfe8 20.Bh3 Rf7 21.g4 Nd6 22.Nxd6 Bxh2+ 23.Kxh2 Qxd6+ 24.Kh1 Rxe2 25.Rxe2 Qd5+ 26.Kg1 Rxf1+ 27.Bxf1 Qf3 28.g5 Qg4+ 29.Rg2 Qd1 30.Bf4 Qf3 31.Rf2 Qg4+ 32.Bg2 Qd1+ 33.Kh2 Qe1 34.Bd5+ Kg7 35.Bg3 Qe8 36.Kg2 h5 37.Rf7+ Kh8 38.Kf1 Qe3 39.Rf8+ Kg7 40.Rf7+ Kh8 41.Bf2 Qc1+ 42.Be1 Qxg5 43.Be4 Qg4 44.Bf2 Qd1+ 45.Kg2 Qg4+ 46.Kh2 Kg8 47.Rf3 h4

The 2022 U.S. Championship is a 14-player round-robin featuring the strongest players in the USA, who compete for $262,000 in prize money as well as the coveted title of U.S. Champion. If two or more players tie for first place a playoff will be held.

Players receive 90 minutes for the first 40 moves followed by 30 minutes for the rest of the game, with a 30-second increment from move one. Draw offers are not allowed before move 30. Official website: uschesschamps.com
